SHELL:

    COMMAND -OPTIONS ARGUMENTS : echo "Hello World !"

    GET USERNAME : whoami

    EXIT FROM SHELL : exit

    LOGOUT FROM SHELL : logout

    POWEROFF SYSTEM : poweroff

    
HELP : 

    GET HELP FOR COMMAND : help command

    GET MANUAL FOR COMMAND : man command

    GET SHORT DESCRIPTION : whatis command

    CHECK WHERE COMMAND IS STORED ; which command


PRINT WORKING DIRECTORY :

    GET PWD : pwd


CHANGE DIRECTORY : 

    CHANGE DIRECTORY : cd Path/To/Directory

    CURRENT DIRECTORY : cd .

    PARENT DIRECTORY : cd ..

    HOME DIRECTORY : cd ~

    LAST ACTIVE DIRECTORY : cd -


LISTING :

    FOR PRESENT WORKING DIRECTORY : ls

    FOR ANY DIRECTORY : ls Path/to/Directory

    LIST INCLUDING HIDDEN FILES : ls -a

        HIDDEN FILE NAME : .StartWithDot

    DETAILED LIST : ls -l

    RECURSIVELY LIST DIRECTORY CONTENTS : ls -R

    SORT IN REVERSE ORDER : ls -r

    SORT BY MODIFICATION TIME : ls -t

    HUMAN READABLE FORMAT : ls -h


TOUCH :

    CREATE FILE : touch "Filename.extension"

    CHANGE TIMESTAMPS : touch Filename

    FILE NAME WITH SPECIAL CHARACTORS LIKE DASH : 

        touch ./-Filename
        touch -- -Filename


FILE :

    DESCRIPTION OF FILE CONTENTS : file Filename.extension


MAKE DIRECTORY : 

    CREATE DIRECTORY : mkdir Directory1 Directory2 DirectoryN

    CREATE DIRECTORY WITH SUB DIRECTORIES : mkdir -p Folder/SubFolder/NextSubFolder


EDITORS : 
    
    OPEN NANO : nano Filename

    OPEN VIM : vim Filename

    
FIND : 

    FILE BY NAME IN DIRECTORY : find /Directory -name Filename

    FOLDER BY NAME IN DIRECTORY : find /Directory -type d -name Foldername


COPY : 

    COPY AND PASTE : cp Source/File/Path Destination/Path

    FILES ENDING/STARTING/CONTAINING WITH : cp Path/To/File/*KeyWord OR KeyWord* OR *KeyWord* Destination/Path

    FILE NAME CONTAINING UNKNOWN CHARACTOR : cp Path/To/File/Known?Name Destination/Path

    FILE NAME INCLUDE OR EXCLUDE KNOWN CHARACTORS : cp Path/To/File/Known[a1b2c3]Name Destination/Path

    RECURSIVELY COPY CONTENTS WITHIN DIRECTORY : cp -r Directory/Path/ Destination/Path

    INTERACTIVE IN CASE OF OVER WRITING : cp -i Path/To/File/ Destination/Path


MOVE  : 

    RENAME OR CUT AND PASTE : mv Source/File_OR_Folder/Path Destination/Path

    GIVE INFO WHAT IS HAPPENING : mv -v Source/File_OR_Folder/Path Destination/Path

    PREVENT OVER WRITING : mv -n Source/File_OR_Folder/Path Destination/Path

    CREATE BACKUP IN CASE OF OVER WRITING : mv -b Source/File_OR_Folder/Path Destination/Path


REMOVE : 

    DELETE FILES : rm File_1 File_2 File_N

    FORCE DELETE INCLUDING WRITE PROTECTED FILES : rm -f File_1 File_N 

    INTERACTIVE IN CASE OF UNWANTED DELETION : rm -i File_1 File_N

    REMOVE DIRECTORY : rmdir Directory1 Directory_N

    REMOVE NON EMPTY DIRECTORIES : rm -r Directory1 Directory_N

    FILE NAME WITH SPECIAL CHARACTORS LIKE DASH : 

        rm ./-Filename
        rm -- Filename


ALIAS :

    CREATE ALIAS : alias nickname='commands'

    CREATE PERMANENT ALIAS : go to ~/.bashrc and add above line

    REMOVE ALIAS : unalias nickname


LINKING : 

    CHECK LINKS INODE NUMBER : ls -i

    CREATE HARD LINK : ln /Path/To/File LinkName

    CREATE SOFT LINK : ln -s /Path/To/File LinkName

    REMOVE LINK : unlink LinkName


HISTORY : 

    LIST ALL PREVIOUSLY USED COMMANDS : history

    RUN LAST COMMAND : !!

    SEARCH COMMAND IN HISTORY : ctrl+R and part of command

    AUTOMCOMPLETE : command + TAB

    CLEAR TERMINAL : clear


